                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">ok - I know one's personal problems can only be solved by talking to the people concerned and not by venting on message boards to complete strangers - BUT - I'm in a lot of pain over a situation and I guess I need all the different perspectives I can get. 
<br />

<br />
I fell for a guy in EQ. Hard. I quietly kept these feelings to myself for months, then imagine my surprise and delight when he started hitting on me. We chatted in game, then over email and my feelings for him exploded beyond belief. I'd never felt like this for anyone, I told all my friends he was the one, and I was terrified of it going wrong. 
<br />

<br />
He obviously like me, but was more distant from me than I was with him - and I worried, and felt I was doing the chasing, but trusted that it would be ok when we met. But after dragging his feel a little, which scared me, he came to visit. We had an (almost) magical time. The 'almost' bit was a nagging voice at the back of my mind that said 'he doesn't feel the same', and the fact rather than being enthusiastic about coming back just to see me (there are practical reasons I cant travel to where he lives atm), he arranged to see me again at a gathering of the whole guild. 
<br />

<br />
When he got back to his own country he went afk for two days, with no contact and I felt full of the old panic. I missed him like hell, and wanted him to come and see me earlier than hed arranged. I wanted to know if he 'really' cared about me. When I asked him to come and see me sooner, he asked me how I felt about the relationship and I felt I had to be honest and tell him I'd fallen deeply in love with him. He told me he wasn't in love with me, but that he took these things slower than me and might come to love me over time. He gave me what felt like a lot of mixed messages. He told me ne was thinking of moving to my country, but that he wouldn't be doing it 'just' for me, even though if it hadn't been for me he wouldnt have been considering it. He told me he didn't want me moving to be with him (I'd have done it like a shot) because it would 'put pressure on him'. He said that "Although I don't love you I feel everything else for you." I didn't know what that meant. 
<br />

<br />
I know from other things he's said that he doesnt belive in marriage or long term commitment (I do) and having dealt with commitment phobes and their selfishness before I was very, very, leery of this and depressed to the pit of my being when I suddenly saw him in that light. 
<br />

<br />
After that conversation I knew something had to change. I sent him a friendly email saying I wasn't asking for commitment at an early stage, but I did want to feel more cherished, and that I wasn't chasing him all the time. That I was going to find it really hard to hack a long distance relationship unless we saw each other more often. 
<br />

<br />
He didn't reply for this for 24 hours. At this point I lost it, and sent him a 'go to hell' email. I layed into him at length I'm afraid, accusing him of just using me for a ****, of being a commitment phobic jerk, of bullshitting me. I told him I didnt want him in my life, and I wanted a guy who would reciprocate my feelings. Then I spent the rest of the weekend feeling like shit - while my friends tried to help me decide if I was being hasty and I should let him take things slowly, or if my instincts that he was backing away from me and I should get out before he hurt me more were correct. They didn't really know any more than I did. 
<br />

<br />
48 hours later I got a short note saying goodbye and that he hoped I found love. He also posted saying hed quit the game.
<br />

<br />
This is a ludicrous train wreck for two adults to get into and I feel I've been stupid beyond belief. I've idealised a guy and then lashed out at him when he didn't live up to it. I want to give him and myself another chance, taking things slowly this time. I have emailed him apologising and telling him all this and saying I really dont want to fall out over email like this and can we talk.
<br />

<br />
But in my heart of hearts right now I feel that this is an irretrievable **** up. 
<br />

<br />
 <img src="images/smiles/icon_hang.gif" alt="icon_hang.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
