                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The trouble with online relationships is that you never really know if you are compatable until you meet. I speak from several failed experiences and one very successful one. 
<br />

<br />
The nagging little voice was telling you the right thing. While he was great online there was something different about him in person. Online we can sometimes alter our behaviors and actions. It is just easier to be nice online and say so many things but when batter comes to plate, some don't even swing. 
<br />

<br />
When you know someone online for a really long time and you meet you can just tell about the whole feel. For the first few hours you are awkward then eventually something will break the tension and if you have been true to one another you will fall into the same comfortability you were online. There are no nagging voices. On the other hand if you always feel like something isn't adding up it would be best to have listened to it and chalk it up as it not meant to be. 
<br />

<br />
*hug* What you did, all be it very passionate in nature maybe was the best thing you did for yourself. There is no sense in chasing what runs away. It will be okay and there were be lots of other guys, online and off. And it's not just the regular rumors you hear, it is true. ^^ You deserve someone who loves you as much as you love them.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://members.shaw.ca/cetra/cetradoll01.gif" border="0" />
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1042318" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Cetra Velioustar</a>
