                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">But in my heart of hearts right now I feel that this is an irretrievable **** up.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Possibly, but since i know neither you nor him it is open to debate.
<br />

<br />
Blokes are normally in a bit of a quandry when it comes to girls. Respond to soon and they are desperate. Respond to slow and they arn't interested.
<br />

<br />
There is also the flip side, he might have been in a serious relationship (to him) and been badly hurt. So he doesn't want to "get serious" with someone again.
<br />
It also sounds like he was considering moving to be close to you, without rushing into it. Being sensible you really don't want to move straight in with someone you don't really know, everyone has their own wierd habits. What if it hadn't worked out, where would he have stayed?
<br />

<br />
Of course the guy could just be a complete jerk and stringing you along for kicks. I unfortuantly know folk that do things like this (my sister dated one for over a year).
<br />
Or he might have been dubious about your side of things.
<br />

<br />
Either way, i don't know what your or his side looks like to the other.
<br />

<br />
To be honest, if he was genuine, he sounds like he is terrified. Sending that hate mail "out fo the blue" is kinda shooting it dead. Moving to another country isn't a small thing, waiting 24hours to respond (he might have had a family emergancy) isn't exactly a long time.
<br />

<br />
Best bet, if you want to find out, is to grovel. Send him a note saying that you are sorry, you were upset (or something). Tell him how you really feel (to be honest it sounds like you are a bit insecure about it all too).
<br />
The hard bit is that you just have to wait. If you don't have anything after about a week send him a short note asking just for a short reply, if nothing else just to confirm that it is over.
<br />
If you don't get a reply to that you can try his family, ask them if its totally over with no chance of reprive.
<br />

<br />
/comfort</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
