                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I sympathize with your situation. To be honest, your friend sounds just like me ... and my impression is that he is a decent, honest and very loyal person. No hidden message, no self promotion or hidden agenda ... what he says is what he means it. You two obviously have a very different style ... which is very good since you will compliment each other and I am guessing that is why you were drawn to him in the first place and him to you. One benefit of online relationship is that you get to know inside before you look at his outside. Relationship takes time so give it a try and be patient ... seems like you two are quite decent people trying to find the right ones.
<br />

<br />
As for sex, I think that it is a wonderful way for two fully committed people to stay together and enjoy each other's love ... strengthening their love essentially ... not a tool for enjoyment. If used too early, it will just end up hurting people and depreciate the special feeling you will have for the one you truly love later on.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=664034" target="_blank" class="postlink">Primer</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
