                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">How can you fix it? That's the question you posed...
<br />

<br />
Do you WANT to fix it? As you've pointed out he dragged his heels in meeting you, and wanted to move nearby but not specificly for you...maybe the other poster was right and he was just using you...but let's hope not...saying he felt everything but love for you is a pretty strange thing to say after all that time. But reiterating this has a point, it *may* be you did move too fast for him. You've said you felt you were chasing him a few times. A guy would rather be sure he's got something to hold on to than continually grasp at straws so to speak. Security and a means of escape > all in a man's life...some basic survival instinct left over from prehistory.
<br />

<br />
Then again...how hard did you slam him in that email? Guys do tend to take those things pretty badly. If they're genuinely meant or not, it does drive a knife through the heart. Some guys don't recover well from that, if at all.
<br />

<br />
If you think there still is some fire left in there somewhere, I'd try to fan it some, swallow a bit of pride maybe. Try if you can to put your feelings on paper or type it up in an email. I mean raw ones, not a feeling you've been mulling over for hours or days. Dont be like me and type this post up like I have been rewriting half of it over and over <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" />. So just going to press 'submit' <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" />.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">V i s i o n a r y . F u n x i</span>.Legendary.tribunal
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4397" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="color: blue">...things I got along the way...</span></a>
<br />
The revolution will NOT be televised.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
